Slaves were considered to be property and thus in accordance with what society knew at the time; females were of lesser value than males. With the emancipation of slaves, it seems that attitudes toward females and marriage has changed. Although in the last decade there seems to be more identified attitudes within feminism and with more women in the workforce; a big issue was access to and the choices women make when it came to marriage. The men that are the respondents in Barnes research have been accused of running away from and not wanting to settle down with one woman any longer. Where this may have been true of their predecessors, Barnes finds that, “in most instances it may be difficult to draw the line of distinction between who prefer 'no strings attached' and who prefer 'committed relationships'”(4).
